## Getting Started

A Git repository is initialized automatically when this project is scaffolded.

Recommended first run:

```bash
cp .env.example .env  # optional reset if you want fresh defaults
go mod tidy
make go
```

Then open `http://localhost:3333`.

Install dependencies:

```bash
go mod tidy
```
{{if has "Tailwind" .Stack.Tags}}
For Tailwind CSS, download the standalone binary:

```bash
make tailwind-install
```

Then build your CSS (or watch for changes):

```bash
make tailwind-build    # Build once
make tailwind-watch    # Watch and rebuild on changes
```

Run Tailwind and the Go server together (installs Tailwind if needed):

```bash
make go
```
{{end}}
Run the development server:

```bash
make dev
# or
go run ./cmd/server
```

These commands attempt to open `http://localhost:3333` in your default browser. Override `APP_URL`
when running `make` if you change the listen address, or export `BROWSER=echo` to suppress opening.

The server will start on `http://localhost:3333`

### Environment (.env)

A ready-to-run `.env` file is generated automatically. The app loads it on startup.
Use `.env.example` as a reference if you need to reset values.

Typical setup flow:

- Open `.env` before the first real run.
- Leave local defaults as-is unless you need a different port or database path.
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "auth-oauth2" }}
- Add OAuth provider credentials for each enabled provider and make sure `OAUTH_CALLBACK_BASE` matches the app URL.
{{- end }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "auth-magic-link" }}
- Set `MAGIC_LINK_BASE_URL` to the public URL you want links to use.
{{- end }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "email-smtp" }}
- Fill SMTP credentials before testing email delivery.
{{- end }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "payments-yookassa" }}
- Fill YooKassa credentials and return URL before testing checkout.
{{- end }}

- `SERVER_ADDR` – listen address (default `:3333`)
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "database-sqlite" }}
- `SQLITE_DSN` – SQLite DSN (empty uses built-in default)
{{- end }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "auth-oauth2" }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "oauth-github" }}
- `GITHUB_CLIENT_ID` – GitHub OAuth client ID
- `GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET` – GitHub OAuth client secret
{{- end }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "oauth-google" }}
- `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` – Google OAuth client ID
- `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` – Google OAuth client secret
{{- end }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "oauth-yandex" }}
- `YANDEX_CLIENT_ID` – Yandex OAuth client ID
- `YANDEX_CLIENT_SECRET` – Yandex OAuth client secret
{{- end }}
- `OAUTH_CALLBACK_BASE` – base URL used to build provider callbacks
{{- end }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "auth-magic-link" }}
- `MAGIC_LINK_BASE_URL` – base URL used to build verification links
- `MAGIC_LINK_TTL_MINUTES` – token lifetime in minutes (default `15`)
{{- end }}
{{- if or (.Stack.HasFeature "auth-oauth2") (.Stack.HasFeature "auth-magic-link") }}
- `SESSION_COOKIE_NAME` – session cookie name (default `sid`)
- `SESSION_TTL_DAYS` – session lifetime in days (default `30`)
{{- end }}

## Available Commands

Run `make help` to see all available commands:

- `make dev` - Run development server with auto-reload
- `make go` - Start development server and Tailwind watcher (if enabled)
- `make build` - Build the application binary
- `make run` - Build and run the application
- `make test` - Run tests
- `make clean` - Clean build artifacts{{if has "Tailwind" .Stack.Tags}}
- `make tailwind-install` - Download standalone Tailwind CSS binary
- `make tailwind-watch` - Watch and rebuild Tailwind CSS on changes
- `make tailwind-build` - Build Tailwind CSS once{{end}}

{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "database-sqlite" }}
### Database Migrations (goose)

Install goose locally and manage migrations:

```bash
make goose-install
make migrate-create name=create_users
make migrate-up
make migrate-status
```

Environment for SQLite DSN and migrations directory can be overridden via `DB_DSN` and `MIGRATIONS_DIR`.
{{- end }}

{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "auth-oauth2" }}
### OAuth Providers (if enabled)

Set the environment variables for each provider you enabled and make sure the callback base matches your app URL:

```bash
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "oauth-github" }}
export GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=...
export GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=...
{{- end }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "oauth-google" }}
export GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=...
export GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=...
{{- end }}
{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "oauth-yandex" }}
export YANDEX_CLIENT_ID=...
export YANDEX_CLIENT_SECRET=...
{{- end }}
export OAUTH_CALLBACK_BASE="http://localhost:3333"
```

Routes available:

- `/auth/{provider}` – start login for the selected provider
- `/auth/{provider}/callback` – provider callback endpoint
- `/profile` – protected page showing user info
- `/logout` – clear session
{{- end }}

{{- if .Stack.HasFeature "auth-magic-link" }}
### Magic Link Auth (if enabled)

Set the following environment variables to activate passwordless login:

```bash
export MAGIC_LINK_BASE_URL="http://localhost:3333"
export MAGIC_LINK_TTL_MINUTES=15
```

Routes available:

- `GET /login` – sign-in page
- `POST /login` – request a one-time magic link (printed to logs)
- `GET /auth/magic/verify?token=...` – verify token and create session
- `GET /profile` – protected page showing user info
- `GET /logout` – clear session
{{- end }}

